000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.011baad1-b973-42a5-a80e-69a38e659175.description=Counts from one number to another number. 
Inputs\:
from - The number to start counting at.
to - The number to count to.
incrementBy - The number to increment by while counting. If unspecified this is 1. If you wanted to count 2,4,6,8 this would be 2.
reset - If true, then the counter will restart counting from the beginning.

NOTE\: These values must be between -9223372036854775808 and 9223372036854775807

Returns\:
The number that was just counted.

Note\: the primary result is resultString, Result can also be used. result (All lower case) should not be used as it is the response code.

Responses\:
has more - Not yet done counting.
no more - Done counting. This will only be returned once, then counting restarts.
failure - Something went wrong.

This workflow returns the list of Artifact’s Properties and values.

Inputs-
artifactId  –  Artifact id
userIdentifier  - User Identifier id
propertyNames – List of property names separated by pipe |
If user provides this inputs, flow will return the values for given property names only. Otherwise flow will return all properties and values for the given artifact.
authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server.
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
Default value\: anonymous - authentication not used when executing the request.
kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for a connection to be established. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A timeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
socketTimeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for the data to be retrieved. This input should be assigned a value greater than or equal to zero. A socketTimeout value of zero is an infinite timeout.
Default value\: 0.
useCookies - If true, enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true.
followRedirects - If true, the GET command automatically follows redirects. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: true
proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - The port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - The username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - The password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - If true, automatically encodes the URL. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value.
Default value\: false.
userAgent - The value that should be used if the HTTP header USER_AGENT has to be overridden.
trustAllRoots - If true, enables weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: true
keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client authentication is not to be used.
keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.

Outputs-
propertyNameValuesList – List of property Names and values
E.g. property 1;value1,value2|property 2;value3|property 3;value3,value4|........

Inputs\: _COMPONENT_ID - Parent Component Id _RESOURCE_BINDING_XML - XML document to add/update resource binding example\: <\!-- id is not required if creating a new Resource Binding id is required for update --> false ACTIVE RESOURCE_BINDING false BOUND bound This is the Resource Filter <\!-- Provide either id or name, both are not required --> Test_SA_April 19, 2012 5\:08\:43 AM UTC 8ab289a336cdcaf40136e35f1a2e21e8 <\!-- id is not required if creating a new Resource Binding id is required for update --> 0 INITIALIZING PRE_TRANSITION Result\: _RESOURCE_BINDING_ID - Added resource binding Id 000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.8765d815-5f3a-4346-87b3-5636da04d622.prompt=Enter a value for proxyUsername 000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.87a4083b-5a40-4742-8318-44f696bf4116.prompt=Enter a value for container 000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.889201b3-128d-408a-8da9-75a33b3530fc.prompt=Enter a value for authType 000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.8a09245a-753d-4132-8126-73f4eba2d80c.description=
Iterates through a list of values. Modifying the value of the list and delimiter inputs during iteration is not generally supported.

Inputs\:
list - The list to iterate through.
separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.
failure - failed to process the list.

Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously.

WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.

Retrieves a column from a table.

Inputs\:
table - A table to get the column from.
rowDelimiter - the delimiter that separates rows in the table.
columnDelimiter - The delimiter that separates columns in the table.
column - the index of the column (Starting at 0) to retrieve from the table.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
A rowDelimiter delimited list containing the elements that were in the specified column.
000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.description=
This workflow adds the Custom based resource offering attached to the infrastructure service component to server group or server component.

Inputs\:

userIdentifier	\: CSA User Identifier 
customResProviderId	\: CSA Resource Provider Id of the Custom provider to be used by the Custom resource binding on the server and server group components.
customOffrName	\: Name of the Custom offering to be attached to the server and server group components.
customBindingOrder	\: Resource binding order of the Custom offering to be attached to the server and server group components.
customOffrId	\: Offering Id of the Custom resource offering.
componentType	\: The component type (SERVER or SERVER_GROUP)
infraComponentId	\: Infrastructure component Id
componentList	\: CSA Component Id of one or more server group (delimited by pipe | operator) OR CSA Component Id of one or more server (delimited by pipe |                                                        operator) 
 		  Eg \: ||.... or
		  Eg \: ||.... 
Responses\:
success - Workflow completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.e37de230-823e-4c7e-8b63-635f8e86ab0d.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists. Default is a comma
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.
000baf59-e0fa-41d7-9bf9-be23fe8783b1.e786ff45-29db-44ae-be43-b6617deaf1a2.description=
Adds flow variables into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyNames - the names of the flow variables to use
myValues - the values to assign the flow variables
delimiter - a delimiter separating values and keys.

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
